                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Admin tooling</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Public UX delivery</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Server-side rendering</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Long-term maintainability</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Hydro International -->
<section id="hydro" class="py-12 sm:py-16 bg-charcoal-900">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-8">
        <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
            <div class="text-accent-500 font-medium mb-2 text-sm">LEGACY MODERNISATION</div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3 sm:mb-4">Hydro International — Legacy System Modernisation</h2>
            <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-charcoal-200 max-w-3xl">
                Hydro International relied on an internal project management and time-tracking system originally built in 2003 using a mix of C# ASP and Ruby. Brought in to modernise the system without disrupting active users or business operations.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 sm:gap-8 mb-8 sm:mb-12">
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE CHALLENGE</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">Business-critical internal tooling with an extremely old codebase. No tolerance for downtime. Existing users depended on current workflows. A full rewrite would have been risky and disruptive.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE APPROACH</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">Incremental, piecemeal migration rather than a big-bang rewrite. Rebuilt functionality gradually in modern Ruby on Rails with Hotwire. Ran old and new systems in parallel during transitions. Improved UX while preserving familiar workflows.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-charcoal-800 border border-charcoal-700 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-2">THE OUTCOME</div>
                <p class="text-charcoal-100 text-sm sm:text-base">A modern Rails 7 application running on Windows infrastructure. Zero downtime for users during migration. Improved usability and maintainability. Reduced long-term operational risk.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div>
            <div class="text-sm text-charcoal-400 mb-3">KEY CAPABILITIES</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Legacy modernisation</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Zero-downtime migration</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Stakeholder collaboration</span>
                <span class="bg-charcoal-700 text-charcoal-200 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs sm:text-sm">Progressive enhancement</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

